First thing to do when performing any kind of penetration test is to perform recon.
We will start this lab by performing an nmap scan. `nmap -sV <target-ip>`

```
### nmap -sV 10.10.10.147
Starting Nmap 7.94SVN ( https://nmap.org ) at 2025-08-21 19:10 CDT
Nmap scan report for 10.10.10.147
Host is up (0.0093s latency).
Not shown: 998 closed tcp ports (reset)
PORT   STATE SERVICE VERSION
22/tcp open  ssh     OpenSSH 7.4p1 Debian 10+deb9u6 (protocol 2.0)
80/tcp open  http    Apache httpd 2.4.25 ((Debian))
Service Info: OS: Linux; CPE: cpe:/o:linux:linux_kernel

Service detection performed. Please report any incorrect results at https://nmap.org/submit/ .
Nmap done: 1 IP address (1 host up) scanned in 7.65 seconds
```
